<br>
Is there a high lvl mage or shaman casting Malo/Mala/malosini on the raid?<br>
If so, you should have way less resist problems <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Can't speak for cold based spells (mages get none, bah!) but found fire worked well.<br>
Clerics of Innorruk have extreme magic resistances, blech <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Spite Golems are ONLY hit by lures.<br>
Wizzies, what lures work best on the golems? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
The drakes are again very resistant you have to really be in melee ranges to land on them, can't remeber whether fire or magic hit best, hm think magic?<br>
Female revenants have very high magic resistance.<br>
The male ones have lowish fire and magic resistances.<br>
<br>
makes sure mobs are well aggroed before casting (ie like 50% health) and cast in melee range if at all possible.<br>
<br>
STAND as soon as &quot;Incoming!&quot; is called. All mobs in Hate are VERY VERY aggro and will mince you if you are sitting or over aggro.<br>
<br>
personally I'd make sure to have decent magic resistance. The liches cast grav flux, and if you aggro the floor above..ugh, its very nasty <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
