<br>
<br>
Listen to the raid leaders, they should take the time to explain everything.  Ask others who have been there before, esp with this particular group.<br>
<br>
Find out your port-in orders.   Stand and fight?  Go for Camp Out?  Gate clear and pray for no interuptes (did that once,  and still died of a DoT before a could get a cure in S Ro).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Most importantly, have fun.  PoH is one of my favorite zones, even with nothing for me there (except the wand of conflag, a nice toy, but nothing more).<br>
<br>
<br>
In the future, I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> strongly</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> urge against Planer trips before level 47.  46 is a Post Hell level, with a harsh death penalty.  It's a very easy level to lose.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
My record for deaths in a Hate raid...   12.  yes, 12.  Including 2 while I was Standing while AFK, during controled pulls (they really liked me that day). <p><TABLE WIDTH=466 ALIGN=CENTER HEIGHT=143 BORDER=1 BGCOLOR=000000>
